Title: Black-bellied whistling duck
Body: The black-bellied whistling duck (Dendrocygna autumnalis), formerly also called black-bellied tree duck.

Title: Fulvous whistling duck
Body: The fulvous whistling duck or fulvous tree duck is a whistling duck that breeds across the world's tropical regions

Title: Snow goose
Body: This goose breeds north of the timberline in Greenland, Canada, and Alaska.

Title: Rock ptarmigan
Body: The rock ptarmigan (Lagopus muta) is a medium-sized gamebird in the grouse family.

Title: Hooded merganser
Body: Hooded mergansers are the second smallest species of merganser.
